{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"alias":"birthstone-moldavite-dunlin","description":"## Reproduction Steps\n1. Run /usr/local/bin/rebar-observability.sh (or systemctl start rebar-observability.service) on a healthy box.\n2. All sections execute and every metric publishes (trace confirms root_pct etc. reach put-metric-data).\n3. The script's last statement is the mirror-out-of-sync guard `[ $oos -gt 0 ] && ...` which evaluates false on a healthy box, and there is no trailing `exit 0` — so the script's exit status is 1.\n\n**Expected:** a run that publishes all metrics exits 0; systemd shows the unit succeeded. **Actual:** exit 1 on every healthy run; journald logs 'Failed with result exit-code' every 5 minutes, the unit sits in failed state (masking real failures and poisoning any future OnFailure/unit-failure monitoring), and install-observability.sh's verification start appears to fail.\n\nObserved 2026-07-10 on the prod box while verifying ac14's root-disk metric (bash -x trace: last line `+ '[' 0 -gt 0 ']'` then exit=1).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] observability.sh exits 0 on a healthy run (e.g. explicit `exit 0` at end, or guard restructured as `if`).\n- [ ] A regression test or shellcheck-style check covers the exit status (mirror the test_autodeploy_prune.py stub-harness pattern if practical).\n- [ ] systemd unit shows active(exited)/success after a timer run on the box post-deploy.\n- [ ] File paths: infra/scripts/observability.sh.","id":"8a37-7eda-d5ac-44d9","parent_id":"","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"bug","title":"observability.sh exits 1 on every healthy run — final statement is a false test with no exit 0"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783703044790166001,"uuid":"eb67a461-e65b-4e27-b407-0fe927a97a0f"}